{
  "video_id": "BQj2Z_GPsY8",
  "title": "How we explore unanswered questions in physics | James Beacham",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7000.0,
      "text": "Translator: Leslie Gauthier Reviewer: Camille Mart√≠nez"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 13870.0,
      "end_time": 17272.0,
      "text": "There is something about physics"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 17296.0,
      "end_time": 21296.0,
      "text": "that has been really bothering me since I was a little kid."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 23100.0,
      "end_time": 24819.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s related to a question"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 24843.0,
      "end_time": 28870.0,
      "text": "that scientists have been asking for almost 100 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 28111.0,
      "end_time": 29280.0,
      "text": "with no answer."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 31108.0,
      "end_time": 34118.0,
      "text": "How do the smallest things in nature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 34142.0,
      "end_time": 36295.0,
      "text": "the particles of the quantum world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 36319.0,
      "end_time": 39350.0,
      "text": "match up with the largest things in nature --"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 39374.0,
      "end_time": 42621.0,
      "text": "planets and stars and galaxies held together by gravity?"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 43250.0,
      "end_time": 46230.0,
      "text": "As a kid, I would puzzle over questions just like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 46470.0,
      "end_time": 48939.0,
      "text": "I would fiddle around with microscopes and electromagnets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 48963.0,
      "end_time": 51158.0,
      "text": "and I would read about the forces of the small"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 51182.0,
      "end_time": 52516.0,
      "text": "and about quantum mechanics"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 52540.0,
      "end_time": 56104.0,
      "text": "and I would marvel at how well that description matched up"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 56128.0,
      "end_time": 57298.0,
      "text": "to our observation."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 58220.0,
      "end_time": 59803.0,
      "text": "Then I would look at the stars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 59827.0,
      "end_time": 62351.0,
      "text": "and I would read about how well we understand gravity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 62375.0,
      "end_time": 65725.0,
      "text": "and I would think surely, there must be some elegant way"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 65749.0,
      "end_time": 68393.0,
      "text": "that these two systems match up."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 69210.0,
      "end_time": 70422.0,
      "text": "But there&#39;s not."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 71673.0,
      "end_time": 72833.0,
      "text": "And the books would say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 72857.0,
      "end_time": 76390.0,
      "text": "yeah, we understand a lot about these two realms separately,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 76640.0,
      "end_time": 78673.0,
      "text": "but when we try to link them mathematically,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 78698.0,
      "end_time": 80270.0,
      "text": "everything breaks."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 80674.0,
      "end_time": 81984.0,
      "text": "And for 100 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 82800.0,
      "end_time": 87360.0,
      "text": "none of our ideas as to how to solve this basically physics disaster,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 87600.0,
      "end_time": 88874.0,
      "text": "has ever been supported by evidence."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 90271.0,
      "end_time": 91925.0,
      "text": "And to little old me --"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 91949.0,
      "end_time": 93759.0,
      "text": "little, curious, skeptical James --"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 93783.0,
      "end_time": 96651.0,
      "text": "this was a supremely unsatisfying answer."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 98110.0,
      "end_time": 100244.0,
      "text": "So, I&#39;m still a skeptical little kid."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 100268.0,
      "end_time": 104780.0,
      "text": "Flash-forward now to December of 2015,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 105290.0,
      "end_time": 107503.0,
      "text": "when I found myself smack in the middle"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 107527.0,
      "end_time": 110467.0,
      "text": "of the physics world being flipped on its head."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 111999.0,
      "end_time": 115318.0,
      "text": "It all started when we at CERN saw something intriguing in our data:"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 115343.0,
      "end_time": 117617.0,
      "text": "a hint of a new particle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 117641.0,
      "end_time": 121857.0,
      "text": "an inkling of a possibly extraordinary answer to this question."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 123777.0,
      "end_time": 125904.0,
      "text": "So I&#39;m still a skeptical little kid, I think,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 125928.0,
      "end_time": 128610.0,
      "text": "but I&#39;m also now a particle hunter."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 128850.0,
      "end_time": 131548.0,
      "text": "I am a physicist at CERN&#39;s Large Hadron Collider,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 131572.0,
      "end_time": 135430.0,
      "text": "the largest science experiment ever mounted."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 135877.0,
      "end_time": 139412.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a 27-kilometer tunnel on the border of France and Switzerland"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 139436.0,
      "end_time": 141286.0,
      "text": "buried 100 meters underground."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 141310.0,
      "end_time": 142464.0,
      "text": "And in this tunnel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 142488.0,
      "end_time": 146441.0,
      "text": "we use superconducting magnets colder than outer space"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 146465.0,
      "end_time": 149526.0,
      "text": "to accelerate protons to almost the speed of light"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 149550.0,
      "end_time": 153427.0,
      "text": "and slam them into each other millions of times per second,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 153451.0,
      "end_time": 156277.0,
      "text": "collecting the debris of these collisions"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 156301.0,
      "end_time": 160272.0,
      "text": "to search for new, undiscovered fundamental particles."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 160727.0,
      "end_time": 163191.0,
      "text": "Its design and construction took decades of work"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 163215.0,
      "end_time": 166247.0,
      "text": "by thousands of physicists from around the globe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 166271.0,
      "end_time": 168811.0,
      "text": "and in the summer of 2015,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 168836.0,
      "end_time": 172260.0,
      "text": "we had been working tirelessly to switch on the LHC"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 172284.0,
      "end_time": 176751.0,
      "text": "at the highest energy that humans have ever used in a collider experiment."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 177735.0,
      "end_time": 180258.0,
      "text": "Now, higher energy is important"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 180282.0,
      "end_time": 182469.0,
      "text": "because for particles, there is an equivalence"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 182493.0,
      "end_time": 184694.0,
      "text": "between energy and particle mass,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 184718.0,
      "end_time": 187179.0,
      "text": "and mass is just a number put there by nature."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 188680.0,
      "end_time": 189386.0,
      "text": "To discover new particles,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 189410.0,
      "end_time": 191531.0,
      "text": "we need to reach these bigger numbers."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 191556.0,
      "end_time": 194810.0,
      "text": "And to do that, we have to build a bigger, higher energy collider,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 194834.0,
      "end_time": 197399.0,
      "text": "and the biggest, highest energy collider in the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 197423.0,
      "end_time": 198889.0,
      "text": "is the Large Hadron Collider."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 200271.0,
      "end_time": 205170.0,
      "text": "And then, we collide protons quadrillions of times,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 205194.0,
      "end_time": 209477.0,
      "text": "and we collect this data very slowly, over months and months."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 210813.0,
      "end_time": 215148.0,
      "text": "And then new particles might show up in our data as bumps --"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 215172.0,
      "end_time": 217617.0,
      "text": "slight deviations from what you expect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 217641.0,
      "end_time": 221608.0,
      "text": "little clusters of data points that make a smooth line not so smooth."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 222379.0,
      "end_time": 224100.0,
      "text": "For example, this bump,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 225100.0,
      "end_time": 227542.0,
      "text": "after months of data-taking in 2012,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 227567.0,
      "end_time": 229696.0,
      "text": "led to the discovery of the Higgs particle --"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 229720.0,
      "end_time": 230925.0,
      "text": "the Higgs boson --"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 230949.0,
      "end_time": 234314.0,
      "text": "and to a Nobel Prize for the confirmation of its existence."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 235972.0,
      "end_time": 239530.0,
      "text": "This jump up in energy in 2015"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 240628.0,
      "end_time": 243920.0,
      "text": "represented the best chance that we as a species had ever had"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 243944.0,
      "end_time": 245421.0,
      "text": "of discovering new particles --"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 245445.0,
      "end_time": 247557.0,
      "text": "new answers to these long-standing questions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 247581.0,
      "end_time": 250678.0,
      "text": "because it was almost twice as much energy as we used"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 250702.0,
      "end_time": 252624.0,
      "text": "when we discovered the Higgs boson."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 252648.0,
      "end_time": 256389.0,
      "text": "Many of my colleagues had been working their entire careers for this moment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 256413.0,
      "end_time": 258489.0,
      "text": "and frankly, to little curious me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 258512.0,
      "end_time": 261423.0,
      "text": "this was the moment I&#39;d been waiting for my entire life."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 261447.0,
      "end_time": 263178.0,
      "text": "So 2015 was go time."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 264654.0,
      "end_time": 266864.0,
      "text": "So June 2015,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 267722.0,
      "end_time": 270381.0,
      "text": "the LHC is switched back on."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 271400.0,
      "end_time": 273917.0,
      "text": "My colleagues and I held our breath and bit our fingernails,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 273941.0,
      "end_time": 276452.0,
      "text": "and then finally we saw the first proton collisions"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 276476.0,
      "end_time": 278432.0,
      "text": "at this highest energy ever."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 278456.0,
      "end_time": 280532.0,
      "text": "Applause, champagne, celebration."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 280556.0,
      "end_time": 284152.0,
      "text": "This was a milestone for science,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 284176.0,
      "end_time": 288798.0,
      "text": "and we had no idea what we would find in this brand-new data."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 291990.0,
      "end_time": 294168.0,
      "text": "And then a few weeks later, we found a bump."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 296192.0,
      "end_time": 297868.0,
      "text": "It wasn&#39;t a very big bump,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 298952.0,
      "end_time": 301464.0,
      "text": "but it was big enough to make you raise your eyebrow."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 301488.0,
      "end_time": 303739.0,
      "text": "But on a scale of one to 10 for eyebrow raises,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 303763.0,
      "end_time": 306373.0,
      "text": "if 10 indicates that you&#39;ve discovered a new particle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 306397.0,
      "end_time": 308123.0,
      "text": "this eyebrow raise is about a four."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 308148.0,
      "end_time": 309298.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 310432.0,
      "end_time": 315643.0,
      "text": "I spent hours, days, weeks in secret meetings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 315667.0,
      "end_time": 318270.0,
      "text": "arguing with my colleagues over this little bump,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 318510.0,
      "end_time": 321287.0,
      "text": "poking and prodding it with our most ruthless experimental sticks"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 321311.0,
      "end_time": 323287.0,
      "text": "to see if it would withstand scrutiny."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 323988.0,
      "end_time": 327449.0,
      "text": "But even after months of working feverishly --"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 327473.0,
      "end_time": 329905.0,
      "text": "sleeping in our offices and not going home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 329929.0,
      "end_time": 332600.0,
      "text": "candy bars for dinner,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 332300.0,
      "end_time": 333599.0,
      "text": "coffee by the bucketful --"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 333624.0,
      "end_time": 337867.0,
      "text": "physicists are machines for turning coffee into diagrams --"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 337891.0,
      "end_time": 339290.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 339314.0,
      "end_time": 341850.0,
      "text": "This little bump would not go away."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 342704.0,
      "end_time": 344842.0,
      "text": "So after a few months,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 344866.0,
      "end_time": 348575.0,
      "text": "we presented our little bump to the world with a very clear message:"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 349457.0,
      "end_time": 352168.0,
      "text": "this little bump is interesting but it&#39;s not definitive,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 352192.0,
      "end_time": 355521.0,
      "text": "so let&#39;s keep an eye on it as we take more data."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 355872.0,
      "end_time": 358163.0,
      "text": "So we were trying to be extremely cool about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 359463.0,
      "end_time": 361651.0,
      "text": "And the world ran with it anyway."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 362383.0,
      "end_time": 364150.0,
      "text": "The news loved it."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 364735.0,
      "end_time": 367290.0,
      "text": "People said it reminded them of the little bump"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 367314.0,
      "end_time": 370737.0,
      "text": "that was shown on the way toward the Higgs boson discovery."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 370761.0,
      "end_time": 373889.0,
      "text": "Better than that, my theorist colleagues --"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 374548.0,
      "end_time": 376865.0,
      "text": "I love my theorist colleagues --"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 376889.0,
      "end_time": 380501.0,
      "text": "my theorist colleagues wrote 500 papers about this little bump."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 380525.0,
      "end_time": 381979.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 382574.0,
      "end_time": 386540.0,
      "text": "The world of particle physics had been flipped on its head."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 387745.0,
      "end_time": 391987.0,
      "text": "But what was it about this particular bump"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 392110.0,
      "end_time": 396101.0,
      "text": "that caused thousands of physicists to collectively lose their cool?"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 397596.0,
      "end_time": 399320.0,
      "text": "This little bump was unique."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 400198.0,
      "end_time": 401567.0,
      "text": "This little bump indicated"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 401591.0,
      "end_time": 404613.0,
      "text": "that we were seeing an unexpectedly large number of collisions"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 404637.0,
      "end_time": 407968.0,
      "text": "whose debris consisted of only two photons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 407992.0,
      "end_time": 409236.0,
      "text": "two particles of light."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 409260.0,
      "end_time": 410497.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s rare."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 411690.0,
      "end_time": 413689.0,
      "text": "Particle collisions are not like automobile collisions."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 413713.0,
      "end_time": 415232.0,
      "text": "They have different rules."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 415256.0,
      "end_time": 417905.0,
      "text": "When two particles collide at almost the speed of light,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 417930.0,
      "end_time": 419351.0,
      "text": "the quantum world takes over."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 419375.0,
      "end_time": 420635.0,
      "text": "And in the quantum world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 420659.0,
      "end_time": 423852.0,
      "text": "these two particles can briefly create a new particle"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 423876.0,
      "end_time": 426655.0,
      "text": "that lives for a tiny fraction of a second"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 426680.0,
      "end_time": 429561.0,
      "text": "before splitting into other particles that hit our detector."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 429585.0,
      "end_time": 432989.0,
      "text": "Imagine a car collision where the two cars vanish upon impact,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 433140.0,
      "end_time": 435283.0,
      "text": "a bicycle appears in their place --"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 435307.0,
      "end_time": 436378.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 436402.0,
      "end_time": 438863.0,
      "text": "And then that bicycle explodes into two skateboards,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 438887.0,
      "end_time": 440680.0,
      "text": "which hit our detector."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 440920.0,
      "end_time": 441471.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 441495.0,
      "end_time": 443448.0,
      "text": "Hopefully, not literally."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 443472.0,
      "end_time": 444813.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re very expensive."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 446191.0,
      "end_time": 449938.0,
      "text": "Events where only two photons hit out detector are very rare."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 449963.0,
      "end_time": 453685.0,
      "text": "And because of the special quantum properties of photons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 453709.0,
      "end_time": 457497.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s a very small number of possible new particles --"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 457521.0,
      "end_time": 459180.0,
      "text": "these mythical bicycles --"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 459420.0,
      "end_time": 461284.0,
      "text": "that can give birth to only two photons."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 461812.0,
      "end_time": 464648.0,
      "text": "But one of these options is huge,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 464672.0,
      "end_time": 467508.0,
      "text": "and it has to do with that long-standing question"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 467532.0,
      "end_time": 470540.0,
      "text": "that bothered me as a tiny little kid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 470780.0,
      "end_time": 471438.0,
      "text": "about gravity."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 473946.0,
      "end_time": 476618.0,
      "text": "Gravity may seem super strong to you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 476642.0,
      "end_time": 480742.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s actually crazily weak compared to the other forces of nature."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 480766.0,
      "end_time": 483397.0,
      "text": "I can briefly beat gravity when I jump,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 484390.0,
      "end_time": 487233.0,
      "text": "but I can&#39;t pick a proton out of my hand."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 488463.0,
      "end_time": 491679.0,
      "text": "The strength of gravity compared to the other forces of nature?"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 492480.0,
      "end_time": 494670.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s 10 to the minus 39."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 494694.0,
      "end_time": 497231.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s a decimal with 39 zeros after it."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 497255.0,
      "end_time": 498412.0,
      "text": "Worse than that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 498436.0,
      "end_time": 501462.0,
      "text": "all of the other known forces of nature are perfectly described"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 501487.0,
      "end_time": 503524.0,
      "text": "by this thing we call the Standard Model,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 503548.0,
      "end_time": 506983.0,
      "text": "which is our current best description of nature at its smallest scales,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 507700.0,
      "end_time": 508163.0,
      "text": "and quite frankly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 508187.0,
      "end_time": 512364.0,
      "text": "one of the most successful achievements of humankind --"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 512388.00000000006,
      "end_time": 516400.00000000006,
      "text": "except for gravity, which is absent from the Standard Model."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 516424.0,
      "end_time": 517573.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s crazy."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 518460.00000000006,
      "end_time": 521146.00000000006,
      "text": "It&#39;s almost as though most of gravity has gone missing."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 522394.0,
      "end_time": 524610.0,
      "text": "We feel a little bit of it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 524850.0,
      "end_time": 525761.0,
      "text": "but where&#39;s the rest of it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 525785.0,
      "end_time": 527670.0,
      "text": "No one knows."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 528300.0,
      "end_time": 532406.0,
      "text": "But one theoretical explanation proposes a wild solution."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 534120.0,
      "end_time": 535459.0,
      "text": "You and I --"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 535483.0,
      "end_time": 537600.0,
      "text": "even you in the back --"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 537850.0,
      "end_time": 539230.0,
      "text": "we live in three dimensions of space."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 539254.0,
      "end_time": 541811.0,
      "text": "I hope that&#39;s a non-controversial statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 541835.0,
      "end_time": 543664.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 543688.0,
      "end_time": 547126.0,
      "text": "All of the known particles also live in three dimensions of space."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 547150.0,
      "end_time": 549340.0,
      "text": "In fact, a particle is just another name"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 549364.0,
      "end_time": 552373.0,
      "text": "for an excitation in a three-dimensional field;"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 552397.0,
      "end_time": 554317.0,
      "text": "a localized wobbling in space."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 555288.0,
      "end_time": 558817.0,
      "text": "More importantly, all the math that we use to describe all this stuff"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 558841.0,
      "end_time": 561914.0,
      "text": "assumes that there are only three dimensions of space."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 561938.0,
      "end_time": 565319.0,
      "text": "But math is math, and we can play around with our math however we want."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 565343.0,
      "end_time": 568509.0,
      "text": "And people have been playing around with extra dimensions of space"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 568533.0,
      "end_time": 569688.0,
      "text": "for a very long time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 569712.0,
      "end_time": 572297.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s always been an abstract mathematical concept."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 572321.0,
      "end_time": 575493.0,
      "text": "I mean, just look around you -- you at the back, look around --"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 575517.0,
      "end_time": 577798.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s clearly only three dimensions of space."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 578954.0,
      "end_time": 580512.0,
      "text": "But what if that&#39;s not true?"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 582109.0,
      "end_time": 588364.0,
      "text": "What if the missing gravity is leaking into an extra-spatial dimension"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 588388.0,
      "end_time": 590344.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s invisible to you and I?"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 591355.0,
      "end_time": 594449.0,
      "text": "What if gravity is just as strong as the other forces"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 594473.0,
      "end_time": 597613.0,
      "text": "if you were to view it in this extra-spatial dimension,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 597638.0,
      "end_time": 600538.0,
      "text": "and what you and I experience is a tiny slice of gravity"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 600562.0,
      "end_time": 602459.0,
      "text": "make it seem very weak?"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 604158.0,
      "end_time": 605333.0,
      "text": "If this were true,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 605357.0,
      "end_time": 608105.0,
      "text": "we would have to expand our Standard Model of particles"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 608129.0,
      "end_time": 612215.0,
      "text": "to include an extra particle, a hyperdimensional particle of gravity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 612239.0,
      "end_time": 615234.0,
      "text": "a special graviton that lives in extra-spatial dimensions."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 615258.0,
      "end_time": 616723.0,
      "text": "I see the looks on your faces."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 616747.0,
      "end_time": 618565.0,
      "text": "You should be asking me the question,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 618590.0,
      "end_time": 622234.0,
      "text": "\"How in the world are we going to test this crazy, science fiction idea,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 622258.0,
      "end_time": 624749.0,
      "text": "stuck as we are in three dimensions?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 624773.0,
      "end_time": 626550.0,
      "text": "The way we always do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 626790.0,
      "end_time": 628218.0,
      "text": "by slamming together two protons --"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 628242.0,
      "end_time": 629394.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 629418.0,
      "end_time": 631982.0,
      "text": "Hard enough that the collision reverberates"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 632600.0,
      "end_time": 634697.0,
      "text": "into any extra-spatial dimensions that might be there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 634721.0,
      "end_time": 637320.0,
      "text": "momentarily creating this hyperdimensional graviton"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 637344.0,
      "end_time": 641724.0,
      "text": "that then snaps back into the three dimensions of the LHC"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 641748.0,
      "end_time": 643570.0,
      "text": "and spits off two photons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 644278.0,
      "end_time": 645616.0,
      "text": "two particles of light."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 647417.0,
      "end_time": 650327.0,
      "text": "And this hypothetical, extra-dimensional graviton"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 650351.0,
      "end_time": 654580.0,
      "text": "is one of the only possible, hypothetical new particles"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 654820.0,
      "end_time": 656217.0,
      "text": "that has the special quantum properties"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 656241.0,
      "end_time": 660477.0,
      "text": "that could give birth to our little, two-photon bump."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 662000.0,
      "end_time": 667820.0,
      "text": "So, the possibility of explaining the mysteries of gravity"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 667844.0,
      "end_time": 671342.0,
      "text": "and of discovering extra dimensions of space --"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 671366.0,
      "end_time": 672958.0,
      "text": "perhaps now you get a sense"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 672982.0,
      "end_time": 677106.0,
      "text": "as to why thousands of physics geeks collectively lost their cool"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 677130.0,
      "end_time": 679120.0,
      "text": "over our little, two-photon bump."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 679360.0,
      "end_time": 681935.0,
      "text": "A discovery of this type would rewrite the textbooks."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 682739.0,
      "end_time": 683891.0,
      "text": "But remember,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 683915.0,
      "end_time": 685639.0,
      "text": "the message from us experimentalists"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 685663.0,
      "end_time": 687902.0,
      "text": "that actually were doing this work at the time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 687926.0,
      "end_time": 689800.0,
      "text": "was very clear:"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 689104.0,
      "end_time": 690278.0,
      "text": "we need more data."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 690302.0,
      "end_time": 691821.0,
      "text": "With more data,"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 691845.0,
      "end_time": 695869.0,
      "text": "the little bump will either turn into a nice, crisp Nobel Prize --"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 695893.0,
      "end_time": 697653.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 697677.0,
      "end_time": 700641.0,
      "text": "Or the extra data will fill in the space around the bump"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 700665.0,
      "end_time": 702531.0,
      "text": "and turn it into a nice, smooth line."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 703515.0,
      "end_time": 704733.0,
      "text": "So we took more data,"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 704757.0,
      "end_time": 707334.0,
      "text": "and with five times the data, several months later,"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 707358.0,
      "end_time": 709480.0,
      "text": "our little bump"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 709720.0,
      "end_time": 711420.0,
      "text": "turned into a smooth line."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 715217.0,
      "end_time": 718701.0,
      "text": "The news reported on a \"huge disappointment,\" on \"faded hopes,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 718725.0,
      "end_time": 721235.0,
      "text": "and on particle physicists \"being sad.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 721259.0,
      "end_time": 723700.0,
      "text": "Given the tone of the coverage,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 723940.0,
      "end_time": 726582.0,
      "text": "you&#39;d think that we had decided to shut down the LHC and go home."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 726606.0,
      "end_time": 727756.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 728628.0,
      "end_time": 730231.0,
      "text": "But that&#39;s not what we did."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 733570.0,
      "end_time": 735710.0,
      "text": "But why not?"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 736475.0,
      "end_time": 739320.0,
      "text": "I mean, if I didn&#39;t discover a particle -- and I didn&#39;t --"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 740209.0,
      "end_time": 743238.0,
      "text": "if I didn&#39;t discover a particle, why am I here talking to you?"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 743262.0,
      "end_time": 745699.0,
      "text": "Why didn&#39;t I just hang my head in shame"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 745723.0,
      "end_time": 746947.0,
      "text": "and go home?"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 751169.0,
      "end_time": 754520.0,
      "text": "Particle physicists are explorers."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 755421.0,
      "end_time": 758373.0,
      "text": "And very much of what we do is cartography."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 759468.0,
      "end_time": 762319.0,
      "text": "Let me put it this way: forget about the LHC for a second."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 762344.0,
      "end_time": 765726.0,
      "text": "Imagine you are a space explorer arriving at a distant planet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 765750.0,
      "end_time": 767750.0,
      "text": "searching for aliens."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 767990.0,
      "end_time": 768621.0,
      "text": "What is your first task?"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 769931.0,
      "end_time": 773700.0,
      "text": "To immediately orbit the planet, land, take a quick look around"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 773310.0,
      "end_time": 774916.0,
      "text": "for any big, obvious signs of life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 774941.0,
      "end_time": 776760.0,
      "text": "and report back to home base."
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 776784.0,
      "end_time": 778408.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s the stage we&#39;re at now."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 779269.0,
      "end_time": 780756.0,
      "text": "We took a first look at the LHC"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 780780.0,
      "end_time": 783640.0,
      "text": "for any new, big, obvious-to-spot particles,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 783880.0,
      "end_time": 785380.0,
      "text": "and we can report that there are none."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 785631.0,
      "end_time": 788304.0,
      "text": "We saw a weird-looking alien bump on a distant mountain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 788328.0,
      "end_time": 790497.0,
      "text": "but once we got closer, we saw it was a rock."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 790816.0,
      "end_time": 793456.0,
      "text": "But then what do we do? Do we just give up and fly away?"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 793480.0,
      "end_time": 794767.0,
      "text": "Absolutely not;"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 794791.0,
      "end_time": 797960.0,
      "text": "we would be terrible scientists if we did."
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 797120.0,
      "end_time": 800733.0,
      "text": "No, we spend the next couple of decades exploring,"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 800757.0,
      "end_time": 802237.0,
      "text": "mapping out the territory,"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 802261.0,
      "end_time": 804626.0,
      "text": "sifting through the sand with a fine instrument,"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 804650.0,
      "end_time": 806108.0,
      "text": "peeking under every stone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 806132.0,
      "end_time": 807685.0,
      "text": "drilling under the surface."
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 808106.0,
      "end_time": 810699.0,
      "text": "New particles can either show up immediately"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 810723.0,
      "end_time": 812856.0,
      "text": "as big, obvious-to-spot bumps,"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 812880.0,
      "end_time": 816821.0,
      "text": "or they can only reveal themselves after years of data taking."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 818103.0,
      "end_time": 822512.0,
      "text": "Humanity has just begun its exploration at the LHC at this big high energy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 822537.0,
      "end_time": 824328.0,
      "text": "and we have much searching to do."
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 824352.0,
      "end_time": 830177.0,
      "text": "But what if, even after 10 or 20 years, we still find no new particles?"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 831530.0,
      "end_time": 832748.0,
      "text": "We build a bigger machine."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 832772.0,
      "end_time": 834346.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 834370.0,
      "end_time": 836600.0,
      "text": "We search at higher energies."
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 836476.0,
      "end_time": 838460.0,
      "text": "We search at higher energies."
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 838946.0,
      "end_time": 841999.0,
      "text": "Planning is already underway for a 100-kilometer tunnel"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 842612.0,
      "end_time": 845588.0,
      "text": "that will collide particles at 10 times the energy of the LHC."
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 845612.0,
      "end_time": 847949.0,
      "text": "We don&#39;t decide where nature places new particles."
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 848366.0,
      "end_time": 850120.0,
      "text": "We only decide to keep exploring."
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 850360.0,
      "end_time": 852593.0,
      "text": "But what if, even after a 100-kilometer tunnel"
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 852618.0,
      "end_time": 854478.0,
      "text": "or a 500-kilometer tunnel"
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 854502.0,
      "end_time": 857343.0,
      "text": "or a 10,000-kilometer collider floating in space"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 857367.0,
      "end_time": 858944.0,
      "text": "between the Earth and the Moon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 858969.0,
      "end_time": 862310.0,
      "text": "we still find no new particles?"
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 863597.0,
      "end_time": 866290.0,
      "text": "Then perhaps we&#39;re doing particle physics wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 866315.0,
      "end_time": 868106.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 868130.0,
      "end_time": 870870.0,
      "text": "Perhaps we need to rethink things."
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 871127.0,
      "end_time": 874388.0,
      "text": "Maybe we need more resources, technology, expertise"
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 874413.0,
      "end_time": 875921.0,
      "text": "than what we currently have."
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 876610.0,
      "end_time": 879951.0,
      "text": "We already use artificial intelligence and machine learning techniques"
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 879975.0,
      "end_time": 881128.0,
      "text": "in parts of the LHC,"
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 881152.0,
      "end_time": 883558.0,
      "text": "but imagine designing a particle physics experiment"
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 883582.0,
      "end_time": 885251.0,
      "text": "using such sophisticated algorithms"
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 885275.0,
      "end_time": 888443.0,
      "text": "that it could teach itself to discover a hyperdimensional graviton."
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 888467.0,
      "end_time": 889624.0,
      "text": "But what if?"
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 889648.0,
      "end_time": 891930.0,
      "text": "What if the ultimate question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 891117.0,
      "end_time": 894589.0,
      "text": "What if even artificial intelligence can&#39;t help us answer our questions?"
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 894614.0,
      "end_time": 896725.0,
      "text": "What if these open questions, for centuries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 896749.0,
      "end_time": 899418.0,
      "text": "are destined to be unanswered for the foreseeable future?"
    },
    {
      "index": 311,
      "start_time": 899442.0,
      "end_time": 902371.0,
      "text": "What if the stuff that&#39;s bothered me since I was a little kid"
    },
    {
      "index": 312,
      "start_time": 902395.0,
      "end_time": 904918.0,
      "text": "is destined to be unanswered in my lifetime?"
    },
    {
      "index": 313,
      "start_time": 906395.0,
      "end_time": 907550.0,
      "text": "Then that ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 314,
      "start_time": 908282.0,
      "end_time": 910376.0,
      "text": "will be even more fascinating."
    },
    {
      "index": 315,
      "start_time": 912144.0,
      "end_time": 915369.0,
      "text": "We will be forced to think in completely new ways."
    },
    {
      "index": 316,
      "start_time": 916361.0,
      "end_time": 918419.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ll have to go back to our assumptions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 317,
      "start_time": 918443.0,
      "end_time": 920782.0,
      "text": "and determine if there was a flaw somewhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 318,
      "start_time": 921401.0,
      "end_time": 924795.0,
      "text": "And we&#39;ll need to encourage more people to join us in studying science"
    },
    {
      "index": 319,
      "start_time": 924820.0,
      "end_time": 927882.0,
      "text": "since we need fresh eyes on these century-old problems."
    },
    {
      "index": 320,
      "start_time": 927906.0,
      "end_time": 931400.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t have the answers, and I&#39;m still searching for them."
    },
    {
      "index": 321,
      "start_time": 931640.0,
      "end_time": 933392.0,
      "text": "But someone -- maybe she&#39;s in school right now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 322,
      "start_time": 933417.0,
      "end_time": 935101.0,
      "text": "maybe she&#39;s not even born yet --"
    },
    {
      "index": 323,
      "start_time": 935783.0,
      "end_time": 938916.0,
      "text": "could eventually guide us to see physics in a completely new way,"
    },
    {
      "index": 324,
      "start_time": 938940.0,
      "end_time": 943208.0,
      "text": "and to point out that perhaps we&#39;re just asking the wrong questions."
    },
    {
      "index": 325,
      "start_time": 944112.0,
      "end_time": 946521.0,
      "text": "Which would not be the end of physics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 326,
      "start_time": 946546.0,
      "end_time": 947952.0,
      "text": "but a novel beginning."
    },
    {
      "index": 327,
      "start_time": 949204.0,
      "end_time": 950353.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 328,
      "start_time": 950378.0,
      "end_time": 952919.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}